args: Er, you appear to have a cat\nfollowing you, {player_name}.
This little guy? Yeah, I saved him from\na wolf attack in the woods yesterday.\nGuess he's taken a shine to me.
He runs off if I get near, though, so I can't\nreally do much else to help him.
Perhaps he just needs some time\nto warm up to people.
In that case, allow me to lend you\na hand in caring for it.
Are you sure? You've been awfully busy\nlately with your magic training.
And yet, I still find time to take care of\neveryone else. Adding one cat to the\nmix will hardly break my back.
...Or so I thought last week.\nI clearly underestimated that cat.

He hasn't lowered his guard even a little.
He won't take meals in front of people,
nor will he so much as sniff the toys
I place in front of him.

He also refuses to eat my food!
That has never happened in my life,
and I am HUNDREDS of years old.
It's simply humiliating.
It's crazy how one little animal\ncan be so much trouble.
Speaking of that picky cat,\nis he not with you today?
No, I haven't seen him since this morning.
Someone heeeeelp! This stupid cat\nwants to eat meeeeee!
GO EAT RANZAL INSTEAD, KITTY!\nHE'S FULL OF TASTY MUSCLE!
No, cat! That's a bad cat!
Thanks, Cleo. *sigh* I don't understand\nhow a cat that follows me everywhere\ncan possibly dislike me so much.
I think he's following you around because\nyou seem like someone he can trust.
Although if that's the case, he could stand\nto be less difficult in his daily...
I simply believe you could stand to be\nless difficult in your daily interactions.
(Those same words were said to ME\nover 300 years ago...)
Honestly, Cleo! Every time King Alberius\nvisits, you immediately put your guard up.
I am not trying to be difficult—I merely\nwish to keep an appropriate distance\nfrom His Majesty.
There is a very fine line between those\ntwo things, and I am not at all certain\nthat you are on the right side of it.
Was it not your abiding respect for\nHis Majesty that led you to this castle\nin the first place?
I simply believe you could stand to be\nless difficult in your daily interactions.
I am an attendant—nothing more.\nIt would be the height of hubris to\nview my liege lord as a friend.

...That said, he has always maintained
that such demeanor is very much like
you—and that it's precisely why you
capture his attention.
I understand your position in this matter,\nbut please try to spare a thought for\nHis Majesty's feelings as well.
(This cat yearns to be near him,\nand yet keeps his distance.)
(I was ever the beneficiary of Alberius's\nunyielding kindness, and yet I...)
Why are you so kind to this cat,\n{player_name}?
Well, I just get the feeling he\nneeds attention.
I feel like I understand this cat—\nand I think he DOES actually\nlike me, deep down.
But he's not taking that next step,\nso I figure it's sort of up to me.
I'm just going to keep trying until he\ntrusts me, which is hopefully going to\nmake him happy in the end.
There is nothing funny about your\nkind and generous nature.
Uh oh. Are you getting cold, little guy?\nHere, you should take this blanket.
Ack! Sorry! Never mind! Forget it!\n*sigh* Maybe this is all a fool's errand.
This cat is well aware of your kindness.
Whew! It sure is cold today.
How about you, cat? You cold?
Heh! See, kitty? It's warmer for both\nof us when you snuggle up like this.
Soon thereafter, Cleo and the prince found a\nsuitable foster family who agreed to take in\nthe cat.
I sure hope he's okay in his new home.
How can he not be? They were practically\nfalling over themselves to pet him and\ngive him food.
And it's all because you taught him how\nwonderful trusting someone can be.
Heh. I guess that makes all my new\nclaw marks worth it.
It seems a chronic and severe good nature\nruns unbroken in your bloodline...
...It was nothing. Shall we head back?
